oul, 1771-1990 (1992) J Korean Meteorol Soc, 28, pp. 125-132; Lim, G.-H., Jhun, J.-G., (1996) Assessment of Climatological Precipitation Amount in the Korean Peninsula in Terms of the Precipitation Records of Korea Raingauge and Precipitation Model Output, p. 165. , (in Korean). Rep KOSEF 93-0700-06-02-3. Department of Atmospheric Sciences, Seoul National University; Liu, W.-L., Changes of drought and flood during the latest 230 years in the Yellow River basin (1992) Proc Int Symp Little Ice Age Climate, pp. 308-314. , Mikami T (ed) Department of Geography, Tokyo Metropolitan University, Japan; Lu, R.-Y., Interannual variability of the summertime north Pacific subtropical high and its relation to atmospheric convection over the warm pool (2001) J Meteorol Japan, 79, pp. 771-783; Murata, A., Reconstruction of rainfall variation of the Baiu in historical times (1992) Climate Since AD 1500, pp. 224-245. , Bradley RS, Jones PD (eds) Routledge, London; Nitta, Y., Hu, Z.Z., Summer climate variability in China and its association with 500 hPa height and tropical convection (1996) J Meteorol Soc Japan, 74, pp. 425-445; Qian, W.-H., Kang, H.-S., Lee, D.-K., Distribution of seasonal rainfall in the East Asian monsoon region (2002) Theor Appl Climatol, 73, pp. 151-168; Qian, W.-H., Zhu, Y.-F., Climate change in China from 1880 to 1998 and its impact on the environmental condition (2001) Clim Change, 50, pp. 419-444; Qian, W.-H., Zhu, Y.-F., Ye, Q., Interannual and interdecadal variabilities in SST anomaly over the eastern equatorial Pacific (1999) Chin Sci Bull, 44, pp. 568-571; Qian, W.-H., Zhu, Y.-F., Little Ice Age climate near Beijing, China, inferred from historical and stalagmite records (2002) Quat Res, 57, pp. 109-119; Richman, M.B., Obliquely rotated principal components: An improved meteorological map typing technique? (1981) J Appl Meteorol, 14, pp. 1223-1235; Richman, M.B., Review article, rotation of principal components (1986) J Clim, 6. , 293-35; Ronberg, B., Wa